tion."],[764,"Body: `{ runId }`."],[767,"Body: `{ runId }`."],[625,"Bootstrap token"],[1054,"Bot setup"],[1494,"Both operations require an admin-scoped token."],[690,"Browser session bootstrap (rate-limited)."],[626,"Browser sessions"],[375,"Budgets"],[394,"Budgets are hard stops, not advisories:"],[852,"Building agents on Runyard"],[1353,"Builds and pushes GHCR `hub` and `runner` container images behind the same two gates, and records both image digests as a release artifact."],[119,"By default a card is blocking: nothing happens until someone decides. Supplying `timeoutMs` or `timeoutAt` at creation makes it a **timed approval**:"],[438,"By default the runner executes workflows directly on its host. Setting `RUNNER_SANDBOX=bubblewrap` on the runner wraps each workflow *launch* in a generated Bubblewrap (`bwrap`) sandbox: the run's workspace is the only writable mount (bound at the same path inside and out), system directories are bound read-only, and the child gets a fresh workspace-local `HOME` — the host home directory, with its keys and credentials, is never mounted. Polling and control commands stay outside the sandbox. Installing `bwrap` is the deployer's responsibility; the runner verifies at startup that the sandbox actually works before claiming runs."],[976,"Cancel; re-queue with same/edited input; merge a successful isolated run into its target branch"],[193,"Cancelling is already an operator act."],[724,"Cannot progress without a specific intervention (`blockedReason` says which)."],[926,"Canonical"],[424,"Capacity and pool"],[376,"Capture paths: what is metered today"],[1070,"Cards are posted to the configured chat with inline buttons (see below)."],[1117,"Cards can deep-link into the Hub as a Telegram WebApp. `POST /api/auth/telegram-webapp` exchanges the WebApp's signed init data for a browser session that is limited to the `approvals` scope — a Telegram identity can review and resolve approval cards, and nothing else. Full app access always requires