oute grammar of the web app and the deep links the API returns."],[1380,"Every operation requires either a bearer access token (`Authorization: Bearer ...`) or a browser session created by exchanging such a token — and the session carries exactly the token's scopes, no extra power. The unauthenticated surface is deliberately tiny:"],[1343,"Every PR and push to `main` (and tags)"],[378,"Every run durably records not just what it produced, but **what it consumed**. Each model call a run's child agents make is captured as a usage record, streamed as a run event while the run executes, aggregated onto the run, and included in terminal payloads — so dashboards, delegated callers, and budget enforcement all work off real numbers, never log scraping."],[629,"Every Runyard API call is authenticated with a **bearer access token**:"],[901,"Every Runyard surface — the web app, the CLI, and the MCP server — is an\nordinary client of one HTTP API served by the Hub. Anything they can do, you\ncan do with `curl`."],[556,"Every schedule has an **IANA timezone** (default `UTC`); the expression is evaluated against wall-clock time in that zone, so DST shifts are honored."],[257,"Every URL in the Runyard web app is shareable: the app is a hash-routed SPA, so any view — a run's logs, a workflow's graph, a pending approval — can be copied from the address bar and opened by anyone with access to the Hub. Links have the form:"],[1255,"Everything durable is in the Hub's data directory (`RUNYARD_HUB_DATA_DIR`,\ndefault `data/`; the `hub-data` volume mounted at `/data` in containers). It\nsurvives every update and rollback:"],[645,"Everything. `admin` is a **superscope**: it satisfies every scope requirement, and admin-only endpoints (tokens, secrets, catalog edits, schedules, hooks, audit) require it."],[480,"Executing on the runner."],[356,"Execution"],[1514,"Execution engine; `\"smithers\"`."],[704,"Execution flow"],[1142,"Execution mode: `local` or `remote` (alias: `--execution-mode`)"],