rior SHA\n(`--from-run <id>` links it to the run being rolled back)."],[156,"Release-notes / social hook point"],[1076,"Request changes"],[1010,"Request changes with a comment; the run is cancelled so it can be re-run with new input"],[1185,"Requirement"],[1171,"Requirements"],[467,"Reruns and promotion"],[915,"Resolve approval cards (approve / reject / request changes) and create them"],[1094,"Resolved cards keep the decision in their `resolution` field (`approved`, `rejected`, `changes_requested`) plus how it was decided (`resolvedVia`: human, fallback timer, engine, policy, or system)."],[1051,"Resolving a card"],[643,"Resolving and creating approval cards only — the narrow scope for approval surfaces."],[149,"Resolving approvals requires the `api`, `mcp`, or `approvals` scope; Telegram WebApp sessions are approvals-scoped by design (see Tokens & scopes)."],[468,"Response endpoints"],[50,"Reusable agent *roles*: a slug, name, description, instructions, a tool list, linked skill slugs, and tags. A role captures \"how this kind of agent should behave\" once, instead of restating it per workflow."],[1177,"Reverse proxy"],[174,"Review stays human-controlled."],[1205,"Role"],[238,"Round-trippable JSON document for a board."],[258,"Route"],[255,"Route grammar"],[960,"Run a workflow: `{input, executionMode, negotiate?}`"],[318,"Run an allowlisted absolute command with declared, typed arguments — never a shell."],[267,"Run artifacts tab."],[995,"Run counts by status, recent activity, attention items"],[393,"Run creation accepts an optional hard spend ceiling — as a top-level `budget` field or `input.budget`, on direct runs, negotiated runs, drafts, schedules, endpoint submissions, and reruns (reruns inherit the previous run's budget unless overridden):"],[263,"Run detail."],[897,"Run drafts"],[1291,"Run drafts"],[1078,"Run hold (default / `custom`)"],[432,"Run lifecycle reports (`start`, events, `complete`, `fail`, artifact upload) are restricted to the runner that owns 