scending timeline (`since=<iso>`, `limit=<n>`); backs `runyard tail`"],[1480,"Unified timeline: status transitions, events, artifacts as NDJSON."],[1130,"Updating a host install"],[1489,"Updating a workflow"],[803,"Updating a workflow bumps its integer `version` and snapshots the previous definition. `GET /api/workflows/{name}/versions` lists the versions observed on past runs, and every run records the `workflowVersion` it executed. Bundle versions count separately, per publish."],[463,"Usage and budgets"],[402,"Usage is captured at the **inference boundary**, through two paths:"],[371,"Usage metering & budgets"],[373,"Usage records and the run aggregate"],[650,"Use for"],[114,"Values"],[1102,"Variable"],[1220,"Variable"],[1241,"Variable"],[22,"Verify the Hub is up:"],[1473,"Verify, in order: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` and `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_CHAT_ID` are set on the Hub; the bot's webhook points at `https://hub.example.com/api/telegram/webhook` with the matching `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET`; the bot is a member of the target chat; and the users pressing buttons are listed in `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_USER_IDS`. Response-endpoint deliveries record their state (`status`, `attempts`, `last_error`) on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`."],[778,"Versioning"],[1331,"Versioning and releases"],[829,"Versions seen on runs."],[259,"View"],[275,"Visual graph tab."],[1448,"Wait and re-run; check the provider account."],[1123,"Watch and manage runs"],[1061,"Web app"],[33,"Web: open **Workflows**, pick &#x2A;*Hello (Smithers proof)**, fill in `topic`, and click Run."],[1055,"Webhook"],[552,"What a fire produces"],[1073,"What each decision does depends on the card's kind:"],[1,"What is Runyard"],[1341,"What it does"],[863,"What it gives you"],[48,"What it is"],[198,"What it matches"],[97,"What it represents"],[1476,"What it tells you"],[1378,"What stays out of public discovery docs"],[1502,"What the workflow does; shown in the catalog and menus."],[1439,"What to do"],[298,"When an a